Package: mr.gmm
Type: Package
Title: Mendelian Randomization Using a Four-Cluster Gaussian Mixture Model
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Yuquan", "Wang", email = "21110700112@m.fudan.edu.cn", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6656-7443")), person("Yue-Qing", "Hu", email = "yuehu@fudan.edu.cn", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5730-0317")))
Reference:
    Yuquan Wang, Yunlong Cao, Dong Chen, Dapeng Shi, Liwan Fu, Anqi Chen, Siyuan Shen, Yue-Qing Hu.
    Pseudo-p-Value-Based Clumping Enhanced Proteome-wide Mendelian Randomization with Application in Identifying Coronary Heart Disease-Associated Plasma Proteins.
    \doi{https://doi.org/10.1101/2025.01.13.25320450}
Description: Perform two-sample Mendelian randomization analysis and generate visualizations of the results.
    The deterministic annealing expectation-maximization (DAEM) algorithm is applied to fit the mixture model.
